result.execSummary:
The defendant Terrance T Travis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Terrance T Travis was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Terrance T Travis is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Terrance T Travis was found guilty of Child Abuse-Intentionally Cause Harm, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).
  • Terrance T Travis was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Count one.

Defendant Terrance T Travis in court with attorney Annamarie Amy Wineke.  Defendant Terrance T Travis in custody.   Abbey DeSiato appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Sarah Zwach, student intern appears under the student practice rule under the supervision of ADA DeSiato.
The court has reviewed all submissions by the state.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements to the court by the state, defense and defendant.
AS to count 1:  Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 3 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prison, consecutive to any other sentence; credit for 64 days served.  Court ordered 1.5 YEARS Initial Term Of Confinement and 1.5 YEARS Extended Supervision.
Court found defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration or Earned Release Programs.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- No further violations of the law.
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- Attend parenting classes.
- Mental health evaluation; take all prescribed medications.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety; random urine screens.
- Attend treatment and/or counseling as determined.
- No violent contact with victim; may not reside with Aisha E. until completion of BIP and approved by agent.
- No violent contact with any children
- Obtain/maintain taxable employment.  Must support self and family.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay all costs, surcharges and supervision fees. Pay all costs, fees, assessments, surcharges that are imposed in count 3.
- Submit DNA sample and pay costs.
FAILURE TO PAY ALL FINANCIAL OBLIGATIONS WILL RESULT IN ENTRY OF CIVIL JUDGMENT.
- Court set restitution at zero.
 
Received and filed: Pretrial Sentence Credit, Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence. 
.
Court advised defendant of penalties for violating the no contact order and due to this DV conviction he may never possess firearms or ammunition.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he must provide a DNA sample, his voting rights are suspended and s/he may never possess firearms.

AS to count 3:  Court sentenced defendant to serve 3 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 1, with credit for 90 days time served.
Court orders all costs, fees, assessments and surcharges (DV) to be paid during extended supervision in count 1.
